summary: This document appears to be an FBI 302 form summarizing trial preparation and evidence identification related to Jeffrey Epstein's Palm Beach house. An individual identified items including sex toys and message pads seen during a search on October 20, 2005.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: Referred to as 'JE' in the context of his Palm Beach (PB) house where evidence was seen.

events.title: Search of Epstein's Palm Beach House
events.description: An individual saw sex toys and message pads in Jeffrey Epstein's Palm Beach house, which were later identified as evidence (GX 294, GX 240, 256, 257, 260, 262, 263).

events.title: Trial Preparation VTC
events.description: A trial preparation session via video teleconference (VTC) was held where an individual identified evidence from the 2005 search of Epstein's house.

keyFacts: Evidence including sex toys (GX 294) and multiple message pads (GX 240, 256, 257, 260, 262, 263) were seen in Jeffrey Epstein's Palm Beach house on October 20, 2005.
The evidence was identified by an individual during trial preparation on November 9, 2021.
The document is subject to a protective order covering specific paragraphs (7, 8, 9, 10, 15, and 17).
